    <fr:title text="Finite relations as matrices over the booleans › "><fr:link href="jms-00IX.xml" title="Finite relations as matrices over the booleans" addr="jms-00IX" type="local">Finite <fr:link href="jms-00IR.xml" title="Relations and matrices" addr="jms-00IR" type="local">relations</fr:link> as <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> over the booleans</fr:link> › </fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We fix a matrix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and compute:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_\mathbb {B}{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j}
   &=
   \begin {cases}
   1 &\text {if } i \mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}} j\\
   0 &\text {otherwise}
   \end {cases}
   \\
   &=
   \begin {cases}
   1 &\text {if } M_{i,j} = 1\\
   0 &\text {otherwise}
   \end {cases}
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {B}]]></fr:tex> is the boolean semiring, any scalar <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\in  S]]></fr:tex> is either <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, we conclude:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_\mathbb {B}{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j} = M_{i,j}
 ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter>
